				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: was: Lambent /now (Twilight)<a name="5985"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 4 03 7:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Scarlet Desert has a spawn cycle in regards to different creatures.  In order to get the named of a specific species to spawn you pretty much need to kill mobs of that species plus other mobs in the area.
<br />
The sunflowers, cheetah's and lightcrawlers are all on the same spawn cycle so if you're looking to spawn sunflowers, kill the sunflowers and also kill cheetah's and lightcrawlers.
<br />
Now comes the annoying part, you might not neccessarily spawn the mob that you were looking to spawn and on top of that the spawn point for these mobs is totally random so camping one spot is not really an option.
<br />
Another thing is that kiting here is next to impossible as there are so many roamers that you'll have a good portion of the zone on top of you in no time flat.
<br />

<br />
Go gather your friends as the camps can be long, on the other hand there are some fairly decent drops off other named mobs and the xp isn't half bad either.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
